@startuml architecture-write-api

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName monospaced
skinparam nodesep 50
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam padding 6

title Write paths to the primary

actor "App without\nDB access" as appA
actor "App with\nDB access" as appB
actor "Co-located app\n(same database)" as appC

note as N1
  **A: OPA-fronted write API**
  OPA verifies the JWT and the writer
  role (WRITER_ROLE in JWT_ROLES_CLAIM),
  injects the subject as audit author,
  then forwards to the fixed-role writer
  (which does no JWT of its own).

  Multi-app: a per-app DB role from a
  JWT claim (DB_ROLE_CLAIM) is
  forwarded as X-Authz-Role; the writer's
  _pre_request() SET LOCAL ROLEs to it,
  so **namespace isolation** applies
  per app.
end note

node "HTTP Write API" as optA {
    component "OPA\n:8181" as opa #LightBlue
    component "PostgREST Writer\n(internal, authz_writer)" as pgrst #Salmon
}

database "PostgreSQL\nprimary" as pg #Orange

N1 -right-> opa

appA -down-> opa : "A: POST /v1/data/authz/write\n(JWT: writer role)"
opa -down-> pgrst : "forward write/delete\n(authorized only,\n+ X-Authz-Role)"
pgrst -down-> pg : "SQL (authz_writer\nor per-app role)"

appB -down-> pg : "B: direct SQL\nwrite_tuple() /\nwrite_tuples_checked()\n(authz_writer role)"

appC -down-> pg : "C: co-located\nbusiness write + write_tuple()\nin ONE transaction"

note bottom of pg
  All three paths land in the same function API
  (SECURITY DEFINER; app roles never get table
  grants) and the same immutable audit trail.
  C additionally makes the grant **atomic** with
  the business change — see the co-located
  topology. Apps whose tuples derive from their
  own DB rows typically feed A or B via a
  **transactional outbox** (MODEL_DESIGN §10).
end note

legend bottom left
  |= Color |= Component |
  | <#LightBlue> | OPA — verifies JWT + writer role, forwards the write |
  | <#Salmon> | PostgREST Writer — fixed authz_writer (or per-app) role, no JWT |
  | <#Orange> | PostgreSQL — authz schema |
end legend

@enduml
